title: Hurts, Pickett hurt; streak ends for 'sloppy' Eagles
description: Eagles QBs Jalen Hurts and Kenny Pickett both suffered injuries in a "sloppy" loss to the Commanders that damaged their chances of getting the NFC's top seed.
author: Tim McManus

title: Colts' Taylor repents for gaffe with 218-yard day
description: Jonathan Taylor made up for a costly gaffe last game by exploding for 218 rushing yards and three touchdowns in a dominant win over the Colts.
author: Stephen Holder

title: 'Everything is so hard' - Amorim searches for answers at Man Utd
description: After a 3-0 humbling by Bournemouth, Manchester United boss Ruben Amorim already has difficult questions to answer.

title: Two-time champion Anderson knocked out by De Graaf
description: Two-time champion Gary Anderson is dumped out of the PDC World Championship on his 54th birthday by Jeffrey de Graaf.

title: NFL scoring updates: Bucs visit Dallas looking to get closer to an NFC South title
description: The Cowboys were eliminated from the playoffs earlier on Sunday, but Tampa Bay aims to strengthen its postseason position. Follow SNF here!

title: Magic's Moritz Wagner suffers season-ending ACL injury, further depleting Orlando's bench
description: The Magic are already without stars Franz Wagner and Paolo Banchero, who both suffered oblique injuries this season.

title: Anderson stunned by De Graaf in shock Ally Pally exit
description: Two-time world champion Gary Anderson crashed out of the World Darts Championship after a shock second-round loss to Jeffrey de Graaf at Alexandra Palace.

title: Team Woods suffer play-off heartbreak at PNC Championship
description: Charlie Woods carded a hole-in-one at the PNC Championship - but it wasn't enough as Team Woods narrowly missed out to Bernhard Langer and his son Jason in a play-off.
